coef_sum <- months %>%
  group_by(city) %>%
  summarise(max = max(estimate))

  geom_point()

Question 1 - Highest and Lowest Seasonal Effect

models <- txhousing %>% 
  group_by(city) %>%
  do(mod = lm(
    log(sales) ~ factor(month), 
    data = ., 
    na.action = na.exclude
  ))

coefficients <- models %>% 
  tidy(mod) %>% filter(grepl("factor", term)) %>%
  tidyr::extract(term, "month", "(\\d+)", convert = TRUE)

coefficients_by_city <- months %>%
  group_by(city) %>%
  summarise(max = max(estimate)) %>% 
  arrange(max)

lowest_3_cities <- head(coefficients_by_city, 3)$city



for(city in lowest_3_cities) {
  message(city)
  plot_data <- coefficients %>% filter(city == city)
  
  ggplot(plot_data, aes(month, estimate)) + geom_point()
  ggplot(plot_data, aes(month, std.error)) + geom_point()
  ggplot(plot_data, aes(month, statistic)) + geom_point()
  ggplot(plot_data, aes(month, p.value)) + geom_point()
}
## McAllen
## Harlingen
## Brownsville
highest_3_cities <- tail(coefficients_by_city, 3)$city

for(city in highest_3_cities) {
    message(city)
  plot_data <- coefficients %>% filter(city == city)
  
  ggplot(plot_data, aes(month, estimate)) + geom_point()
  ggplot(plot_data, aes(month, std.error)) + geom_point()
  ggplot(plot_data, aes(month, statistic)) + geom_point()
  ggplot(plot_data, aes(month, p.value)) + geom_point()
}
## San Marcos
## Galveston
## Bryan-College Station
